I remember this particular scene very well.
It was our last day in Newfoundland, our last chance to capture some unique perspective. After circling back and forth the fjord that was covered in deep fog, suddenly a faint glow appeared. As the sea mist lifted, hues were turning from vivid blues to vibrant reds and back, once the blue hour started to take over. Icebergs that were left hidden, emerged and everything aligned as I had dreamt about.. #newfoundland

Summer on Lofoten, shot on Contax T2.
